{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":6,"question":"Kevin nearly drove into the truck in front of him when it stopped _____. He stepped hard on the brakes and just managed to avoid crashing into it.","translation":"前のトラックが突然止まったとき、ケビンは危うく追突しそうになった。彼は強くブレーキを踏み、なんとか衝突を避けた。","choices":["indifferently","appealingly","abruptly","timidly"],"answer":3,"explanation":"nearly drove into, stepped hard on the brakes から『突然』止まったと分かる。","choice_notes":["indifferently=無関心に","appealingly=魅力的に、訴えるように","abruptly=突然に","timidly=臆病に"],"synonyms":"suddenly, unexpectedly, all at once"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":7,"question":"The professor told the class that she would not _____ lateness. She said that any papers not turned in on time would receive a failing grade.","translation":"教授は授業で、遅れを容認しないと言った。期限までに提出されないレポートは不合格点になると言った。","choices":["clarify","implement","tolerate","humiliate"],"answer":3,"explanation":"not turned in on time would receive a failing grade から、遅れを『許さない』。tolerate = 容認する。","choice_notes":["clarify=明確にする","implement=実施する","tolerate=容認する","humiliate=恥をかかせる"],"synonyms":"allow, accept, put up with, endure"},
