{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":9,"question":"A: Majid, remind me how many people we can _____ in Conference Room B. B: Fifteen, so it should be fine for today’s meeting.","translation":"A: マジッド、会議室Bに何人収容できるか教えて。B: 15人だから、今日の会議には大丈夫なはずだ。","choices":["outlaw","elevate","plead","accommodate"],"answer":4,"explanation":"Conference Room B と Fifteen から『収容する』。accommodate は人数・客を収容する。","choice_notes":["outlaw=違法にする","elevate=高める","plead=嘆願する","accommodate=収容する、対応する"],"synonyms":"hold, fit, house, seat"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":10,"question":"The company president was not _____ about the reasons for the layoffs. When asked, he gave only vague answers and avoided any direct comments.","translation":"会社の社長は解雇の理由について率直ではなかった。尋ねられても曖昧な答えだけをし、直接的なコメントを避けた。","choices":["alleged","forthcoming","blissful","fainthearted"],"answer":2,"explanation":"vague answers, avoided direct comments から『率直でない』。not forthcoming = 情報を進んで出さない。","choice_notes":["alleged=申し立てられた","forthcoming=率直な、近く来る","blissful=この上なく幸せな","fainthearted=臆病な"],"synonyms":"open, frank, candid, informative"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":11,"question":"The politician claimed he was _____ to no one, but everyone knew he had received donations from many companies to help his campaign.","translation":"その政治家は誰にも恩義はないと主張したが、選挙活動を助けるため多くの会社から寄付を受けていたことを皆が知っていた。","choices":["sinister","indebted","perilous","doomed"],"answer":2,"explanation":"donations from many companies がヒント。indebted to は『〜に恩義がある、借りがある』。","choice_notes":["sinister=不吉な、邪悪な","indebted=恩義がある、借金がある","perilous=危険な","doomed=運命づけられた、破滅する"],"synonyms":"obligated, owing, grateful"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":12,"question":"Parents were asked to _____ their children to and from the school dance. Since the event would be held in the evening, school officials did not want children going on their own.","translation":"保護者は、学校のダンスイベントへの行き帰りに子どもを付き添うよう求められた。イベントは夜に行われるため、学校側は子どもだけで行かせたくなかった。","choices":["appoint","import","acquaint","escort"],"answer":4,"explanation":"to and from, did not want children going on their own から『付き添う』。escort = 付き添う。","choice_notes":["appoint=任命する","import=輸入する","acquaint=知らせる、知り合いにする","escort=付き添う、護衛する"],"synonyms":"accompany, guide, chaperone"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":13,"question":"The cookie factory made one _____ of cookies with salt instead of sugar. They had to throw the entire lot away.","translation":"そのクッキー工場は、砂糖の代わりに塩を入れたクッキーを1ロット作ってしまった。その全体を廃棄しなければならなかった。","choices":["aggression","substitute","relegation","batch"],"answer":4,"explanation":"one ... of cookies, entire lot がヒント。batch は『一度に作られる一まとまり』。","choice_notes":["aggression=攻撃性","substitute=代用品","relegation=降格","batch=一束、一回分の生産量"],"synonyms":"lot, group, set, production run"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":14,"question":"The documentary on the war was so powerful that it _____ strong feelings of sadness and anger in the viewers.","translation":"その戦争のドキュメンタリーは非常に力強く、視聴者に悲しみと怒りの強い感情を呼び起こした。","choices":["dehydrated","evoked","acquired","posed"],"answer":2,"explanation":"strong feelings ... in the viewers と相性がよいのは evoke『感情を呼び起こす』。","choice_notes":["dehydrate=脱水状態にする","evoke=呼び起こす","acquire=獲得する","pose=提示する、ポーズを取る"],"synonyms":"aroused, triggered, stirred, brought out"},
{"year":"2025","session":"1","grade":"Pre-1","qno":15,"question":"The travel agent warned the couple not to _____ the discount airline’s flights being on time. They were often delayed or canceled.","translation":"旅行代理店は、その夫婦に格安航空会社の便が時間通りであることを当てにしないよう警告した。それらはよく遅れたりキャンセルされたりしていた。","choices":["take in","even out","figure on","make do"],"answer":3,"explanation":"not to figure on = 〜を当てにしない。delayed or canceled がヒント。","choice_notes":["take in=取り込む、だます、理解する","even out=均一にする","figure on=当てにする、予想する","make do=何とかやりくりする"],"synonyms":"count on, rely on, expect, bank on"},
