{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":1,"question":"The men who escaped from prison _____ the police for three weeks, but they were finally caught and brought back.","translation":"刑務所から逃げた男たちは3週間警察から逃れたが、ついに捕まり連れ戻された。","choices":["evaded","sterilized","wrecked","commuted"],"answer":1,"explanation":"escaped, finally caught がヒント。evade the police = 警察から逃れる。","choice_notes":["evade=逃れる、回避する","sterilize=殺菌する、不妊化する","wreck=破壊する","commute=通勤する、減刑する"],"synonyms":"avoid, escape, elude, dodge"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":2,"question":"The novel was fascinating because it told the same story from several different _____. Each character saw the events in a very different way.","translation":"その小説は、同じ物語をいくつかの異なる視点から語っていたので魅力的だった。各登場人物は出来事をまったく違う見方で見ていた。","choices":["reductions","nominations","maneuvers","perspectives"],"answer":4,"explanation":"Each character saw the events... が perspective『視点』の説明。","choice_notes":["reduction=削減","nomination=指名","maneuver=策略、操作","perspective=視点、見方"],"synonyms":"viewpoint, point of view, angle, outlook"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":3,"question":"Although the bedrooms in the apartment were quite _____, the kitchen and dining room were small, so the couple decided not to rent it.","translation":"そのアパートの寝室はかなり広かったが、台所と食堂が狭かったので、その夫婦は借りないことにした。","choices":["supernatural","cowardly","spacious","compliant"],"answer":3,"explanation":"the kitchen and dining room were small との対比。spacious = 広々とした。","choice_notes":["supernatural=超自然的な","cowardly=臆病な","spacious=広々とした","compliant=従順な、準拠した"],"synonyms":"roomy, large, expansive, ample"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":4,"question":"The university will hold an event next month for graduating high school students who are thinking of _____ there next semester.","translation":"その大学は来月、来学期にそこへ入学することを考えている高校卒業予定者向けのイベントを開催する。","choices":["enrolling","rebelling","radiating","solidifying"],"answer":1,"explanation":"university, graduating high school students, next semester から enrolling『入学する』。","choice_notes":["enroll=入学する、登録する","rebel=反抗する","radiate=放射する","solidify=固める"],"synonyms":"register, sign up, enter, matriculate"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":5,"question":"Although the actual battle lasted for almost a week, the writer decided to _____ all the events into one day in his novel to make it more dramatic.","translation":"実際の戦いはほぼ1週間続いたが、作家は小説をより劇的にするため、すべての出来事を1日に圧縮することにした。","choices":["inhale","haunt","obstruct","compress"],"answer":4,"explanation":"almost a week を one day にするので compress『圧縮する』。","choice_notes":["inhale=吸い込む","haunt=つきまとう","obstruct=妨げる","compress=圧縮する"],"synonyms":"condense, squeeze, shorten, compact"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":6,"question":"The _____ between the two neighboring teams is very strong. Sometimes, the players have even fought during games.","translation":"隣り合う2チームのライバル関係はとても強い。試合中に選手同士がけんかをしたことさえある。","choices":["forgery","candidacy","leniency","rivalry"],"answer":4,"explanation":"two neighboring teams, fought during games が rivalry『対抗意識、ライバル関係』。","choice_notes":["forgery=偽造","candidacy=立候補","leniency=寛大さ","rivalry=ライバル関係"],"synonyms":"competition, contest, feud"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":7,"question":"A: Are you going anywhere for spring vacation, George? B: I have _____ plans to visit Spain, but I haven’t booked anything yet.","translation":"A: 春休みにどこか行くの、ジョージ？ B: スペインに行く仮の計画はあるけど、まだ何も予約していない。","choices":["nutritious","righteous","tentative","universal"],"answer":3,"explanation":"haven’t booked anything yet が『まだ確定ではない』。tentative = 仮の。","choice_notes":["nutritious=栄養のある","righteous=正義の、道徳的な","tentative=仮の、不確かな","universal=普遍的な"],"synonyms":"provisional, uncertain, not final, preliminary"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":8,"question":"Medical students spend a lot of time studying human _____. They must memorize the terms for even the smallest parts of the body.","translation":"医学生は人体解剖学の勉強に多くの時間を費やす。体の最も小さな部分の名称まで覚えなければならない。","choices":["reprimand","anatomy","esteem","distress"],"answer":2,"explanation":"parts of the body が anatomy『解剖学、体の構造』を示す。","choice_notes":["reprimand=叱責","anatomy=解剖学、体の構造","esteem=尊敬","distress=苦痛"],"synonyms":"body structure, morphology"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":9,"question":"While the _____ of the mountain took them two days, the climbers were able to come down in less than twelve hours.","translation":"登山には2日かかったが、登山者たちは12時間未満で下山できた。","choices":["warranty","fracture","hazard","ascent"],"answer":4,"explanation":"come down との対比。ascent = 登ること。","choice_notes":["warranty=保証","fracture=骨折、破損","hazard=危険","ascent=上昇、登山"],"synonyms":"climb, rise, upward journey"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":10,"question":"The two fighter jets were flying so close to one another that the pilot of one of them was afraid they would _____.","translation":"2機の戦闘機が互いに非常に近くを飛んでいたので、そのうち1機のパイロットは衝突するのではないかと恐れた。","choices":["abide","collide","subside","preside"],"answer":2,"explanation":"flying so close がヒント。collide = 衝突する。","choice_notes":["abide=従う、我慢する","collide=衝突する","subside=弱まる、沈下する","preside=議長を務める"],"synonyms":"crash, hit, bump into"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":11,"question":"After carefully removing the screws, the technician was able to _____ the power supply from the computer and replace it with a newer model.","translation":"ねじを慎重に外した後、技術者はコンピューターから電源装置を取り外し、新しいモデルと交換することができた。","choices":["detach","tame","unfold","bundle"],"answer":1,"explanation":"removing the screws, replace it が detach『取り外す』を示す。","choice_notes":["detach=取り外す、切り離す","tame=飼いならす","unfold=広げる、展開する","bundle=束ねる"],"synonyms":"remove, disconnect, separate, take off"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":12,"question":"The company gave its salespeople _____ over their daily work. They are now free to make their own decisions without having to get approval from management.","translation":"会社は営業担当者に日々の仕事に関する自主性を与えた。彼らは今、経営陣の承認を得ることなく自分で決定できる。","choices":["ransom","precaution","autonomy","conservation"],"answer":3,"explanation":"free to make their own decisions が autonomy『自主性』の説明。","choice_notes":["ransom=身代金","precaution=予防策","autonomy=自主性、自治","conservation=保護、保存"],"synonyms":"independence, freedom, self-government"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":13,"question":"New Croix City is known for its _____ culture. People from all over the world come to live in the city, and it is famous for its diverse restaurants and neighborhoods.","translation":"ニュークロワ市は国際的な文化で知られている。世界中から人々が住みに来ており、多様なレストランや地区で有名だ。","choices":["gloomy","tender","cosmopolitan","menacing"],"answer":3,"explanation":"People from all over the world, diverse が cosmopolitan『国際的な』。","choice_notes":["gloomy=暗い、悲観的な","tender=優しい、柔らかい","cosmopolitan=国際的な、世界的な","menacing=脅迫的な"],"synonyms":"international, multicultural, worldly, global"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":14,"question":"The little girl had a _____ in her eye as she told her grandmother about the new puppy her mother had given her. It was clear she was very happy.","translation":"母親にもらった新しい子犬について祖母に話すとき、その少女の目はきらきらしていた。彼女がとても幸せなのは明らかだった。","choices":["perch","breeze","gleam","sizzle"],"answer":3,"explanation":"in her eye, very happy から gleam『きらめき』。","choice_notes":["perch=止まり木、腰掛ける","breeze=そよ風","gleam=きらめき","sizzle=ジュージュー音を立てる"],"synonyms":"sparkle, glint, shine, twinkle"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":15,"question":"The children were hungry, so the couple decided to _____ the nearest town. They thought they could find a restaurant there.","translation":"子どもたちがお腹をすかせていたので、その夫婦は最寄りの町へ向かうことにした。そこならレストランを見つけられると思った。","choices":["live off","make for","pass on","wipe out"],"answer":2,"explanation":"nearest town へ向かうので make for = 〜へ向かう。","choice_notes":["live off=〜に頼って生活する","make for=〜へ向かう、役立つ","pass on=伝える、辞退する","wipe out=全滅させる"],"synonyms":"head for, go toward, proceed to"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":16,"question":"Julia has decided her son, Rob, is old enough to _____ more responsibilities at home, so she will give him two additional jobs to do on weekends.","translation":"ジュリアは、息子のロブが家庭でより多くの責任を引き受けるのに十分な年齢だと判断したので、週末にする仕事を2つ追加で与えることにした。","choices":["iron out","toss in","take on","size up"],"answer":3,"explanation":"more responsibilities と相性が良いのは take on『引き受ける』。","choice_notes":["iron out=問題を解決する","toss in=おまけに入れる","take on=引き受ける","size up=評価する"],"synonyms":"undertake, assume, accept, shoulder"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":17,"question":"The company wants to try all other options first, but it cannot _____ reducing its staff if its poor sales continue.","translation":"会社はまず他のすべての選択肢を試したいが、売上不振が続けば人員削減を除外することはできない。","choices":["sound off","draw back","turn up","rule out"],"answer":4,"explanation":"cannot rule out = 〜を除外できない、可能性を否定できない。","choice_notes":["sound off=大声で意見を言う","draw back=後退する、ためらう","turn up=現れる、音量を上げる","rule out=除外する"],"synonyms":"exclude, eliminate, dismiss, reject"},
{"year":"2025","session":"3","grade":"Pre-1","qno":18,"question":"The movie star asked the journalist to _____ after the interview. She promised to give him an exclusive story if he did.","translation":"その映画スターはインタビュー後、記者にその場に残るよう頼んだ。そうすれば独占記事を提供すると約束した。","choices":["chip in","pull off","stick around","bear up"],"answer":3,"explanation":"after the interview, give exclusive story if he did から、その場に残る。stick around = 近くにいる、残る。","choice_notes":["chip in=お金を出し合う、口を挟む","pull off=成功させる","stick around=残る、その場にいる","bear up=耐える"],"synonyms":"stay, remain, wait around"},
